great demos, Mike! I've been working through the learningwebgl.com lessons with haXe using your Mat4.hx file. I noticed when using the rotate method that my cube was stretching when rotating around more than one axis at the same time. Adding a bit of code to normalize the passed vector fixed it like: 

public function rotate(theta, x:Float, y:Float, z:Float) 
	{				
		var len:Float = Math.sqrt(x * x + y * y + z * z);
		if (len != 1) {
			len = 1.0 / len;
			x *= len;
			y *= len;
			z *= len;
		} 
                ...

so just thought I'd let you know in case you use it for some 3D stuff ; )
